Creating images with R with a little bit of magick

Deanna Shea

2023-03-11

#My meme

My cat, Nala, is always up for treats and does not take NO for answer! 

#square one
confused_cat <- confused_cat <- image_read("https://imgflip.com/s/meme/Scared-Cat.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

#square two
Treats_text <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                           height = 500, 
                           color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Treats no more?",
                 color = "#ff6699",
                 size = 60,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

cat_vector <- c(confused_cat, Treats_text)

meme <- image_append(cat_vector, stack = TRUE)
image_write(meme, “my_meme.png”)

My animated GIF

I wanted to apply zoom in feautures and use different font and size of the text to make it funny as the cat face is aboslutly adorable. 

#creating animation
confused_cat <- image_read("https://imgflip.com/s/meme/Scared-Cat.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)
# creating each frame
frame1 <- confused_cat %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Treats no moRe?", color = "yellow", font = "impact", size = 30, gravity = "southwest") %>%
  image_scale(200) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")
frame2 <- confused_cat %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Treats no moRe?", color = "white", size = 50, gravity = "southeast") %>%
  image_scale(300) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")
frame3 <- confused_cat %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Treats no moRe?", color = "green", font = "impact", size = 65, gravity = "north") %>%
  image_scale(400) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")
frame4 <- confused_cat %>%
  image_annotate(text = "NO moRe?",color = "orange", font = "Impact", size = 80, gravity = "south") %>%
  image_scale(500)
# putting the frames together
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)
# animation ready
animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 1)
image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
